DIGEST
SB 220 Original 2026 Regular Session Talbot
Present law provides that the secretary of state shall take all necessary actions for the acts
and joint resolutions of the legislature to be accessible on the internet and the Official
Journal of the State.
Proposed law removes the requirement to make acts and resolutions accessible on the
internet website or portal of the Official Journal of the State and requires the secretary of
state to transmit the acts and joint resolutions of the legislature to the Official Journal of the
State.
Effective August 1, 2026.
(Amends R.S. 43:24(C))
